						<summary>

						<p>On a rock near the pond close to the Rāmaliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Aśōka.</p>						

						<p>Undated. Written in the Prākṛit language and Brāhmī script of 3rd century B.C.</p>						

						<p>It contains two Minor Rock Edicts of the king Aśoka, varying slightly from the version in the Eṟṟaguḍi edict.</p>						

						<p>(Inscription published in <hi rend="italic">Epigraphia Indica,</hi> Vol. XXXI, pp. 211 ff).</p>						

						</summary>
